thread.title: High Pressure Keeps Rain Away, Sunshine Dominates Forecast
thread.title_full: High Pressure Keeps Rain Away, Sunshine Dominates Forecast

author: Chris Holtzman
title: High Pressure Keeps Rain Away, Sunshine Dominates Forecast
text:
JACKSONVILLE, Fla. â€“ Tonight will be clear and chilly with temperatures in the 30s and 40s. Patchy frost will be possible Saturday morning, especially north and west of the metro where temperatures will drop into the low to mid 30s.
Tonight's low temperatures. A Frost Advisory is in effect for Saturday morning for part of our area. Make sure to take protective measures if you have any outdoor plants.
Weekend forecast. High pressure will build overhead this weekend, which will bring more sunshine to our area and above normal temperatures. Highs on Saturday will be near 70 degrees, low to mid 70s on Sunday.
Surface map early next week. Looking ahead to next week, high pressure will remain overhead. Little if any rain is in sight through next weekend. Temperatures will remain above normal with highs in the 70s. Monday will be breezy and the breeze will diminish on Tuesday.
TONIGHT: Clear Sky. Low 40.
SATURDAY: Sunny Sky. High 70, Low 44.
SUNDAY: Mostly Sunny. High 72, Low 49.
MONDAY: Partly Cloudy & Breezy. High 65, Low 55.
TUESDAY: Sun & Clouds. High 72, Low 51.
WEDNESDAY: Mostly Sunny. High 74, Low 50.
THURSDAY: Mostly Sunny. High 75, Low 57.
